    "body": "> one thing I'm not sure about with this implementation is that it puts some complexity that's only relevant for tests in a main example. I'd rather see the same code multiple times than this factorisation (if anything needs to change we already need to do it in three flavours anyway)\r\n\r\nI see what you mean. I tried to make it simple but I guess it's still not helpful for customers who will rely on these main examples to learn InstantSearch.js.\r\n\r\nI'll copy the example to have a dedicated UMD implementation then.",
